ation"},{"authors":[],"categories":[],"content":"You need to compute a subset of the outputs of a 2D FFT with a large zero padding? Try PrunedFFT.jl. It works also on GPUüî•\nusing PrunedFFT n = 128 x = rand(n, n) n_pad = 1024 k_span = collect(512:612) f = pruned_fft(x, n_pad, k_span) If CUDA.jl is installed\nusing CUDA xc = cu(x) f = pruned_fft(xc, n_pad, k_span) For a very large zero padding, GPUüî• acceleration is a must!\njulia\u0026gt; @time f1 = pruned_fft(xc, n_pad^2, k_span); 0.713510 seconds (78.25 k allocations: 1.792 GiB, 17.73% gc time) julia\u0026gt; @time f1 = pruned_fft(x, n_pad^2, k_span); 19.362908 seconds (2.25 k allocations: 9.985 GiB, 3.82% gc time) ","date":1695308140,"expirydate":-62135596800,"kind":"page","lang":"en","lastmod":1695308140,"objectID":"f89b6ec4d43d1c4fa78bd51d37f73056","permalink":"http://localhost:49676/post/prunedfft/","publishdate":"2023-09-21T16:55:40+02:00","relpermalink":"/post/prunedfft/","section":"post","summary":"You need to compute a subset of the outputs of a 2D FFT with a large zero padding? Try PrunedFFT.jl. It works also on GPUüî•\nusing PrunedFFT n = 128 x = rand(n, n) n_pad = 1024 k_span = collect(512:612) f = pruned_fft(x, n_pad, k_span) If CUDA.","tags":[],"title":"PrunedFFT","type":"post"},{"authors":["X. Wang","R. A. Borsoi","C. Richard","A. Ferrari"],"categories":null,"content":"","date":1693526400,"expirydate":-62135596800,"kind":"page","lang":"en","lastmod":1693526400,"objectID":"57d0af6bfcf544deefd0789e01b37061","permalink":"http://localhost:49676/publication/gretsi-23/","publishdate":"2025-04-01T13:38:31.396076Z","relpermalink":"/publication/gretsi-23/","section":"publication","summary":"","tags":null,"title":"D√©tection de changements dans des signaux sur graphe √† valeur dans des varitÃÅ' ÃÅriemanniennes","type":"publication"},{"authors":["A. Ferrari","C. Richard","A. Bourrier","I. Bouchikhi"],"categories":null,"content":"","date":1672531200,"expirydate":-62135596800,"kind":"page","lang":"en","lastm